# Bounded contexts (modular monolith)

Single Maven module; logical boundaries in `dev.vepo.contraponto.*`. Full table: [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) §Bounded contexts. CDI events: [docs/cdi-events.md](../../docs/cdi-events.md).

## Context map

| Context | Packages |
|---------|----------|
| Shared kernel | `shared` |
| Identity & access | `auth`, `user` |
| Content publishing | `blog`, `post`, `write`, `tag`, `serie`, `renderer`, `content` |
| Reader engagement | `notification`, `comment`, `readinglist`, `readingtime`, `highlight`, `postresponse` |
| Discovery & syndication | `home`, `search`, `directory`, `rss`, `seo`, `view` |
| Media | `image` |
| Customization | `custompage` |
| Integration | `git`, `activitypub` |
| Author workspace | `library`, `dashboard`, `admin`, `profile` |
| Presentation shell | `components`, `navigation` |
| Platform insights | `platforminsights` |

## Dependency rules

- Feature contexts **may depend on** `shared` and contexts listed in the domain spec table for that row.
- **`shared` kernel** must not import other `dev.vepo.contraponto.*` packages (except during documented migration).
- **`..*Repository`** must not depend on `..*Endpoint` or `..*Service` ([contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc](contraponto-layered-architecture.mdc)).
- **Cross-context side effects:** use CDI events (`PostPublishedEvent`, `CustomPageChangedEvent`, …) — not service calls from publishing into notification/RSS/SEO/Git.
- **`@TemplateExtension`** classes belong in the owning context package, not `shared.infra`.
- **Presentation shell** may compose endpoints across contexts at the HTTP boundary only.

## Enforcement

ArchUnit tests in `src/test/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/architecture/BoundedContextRulesTest.java` — keep green on every change (bounded-context deps, PascalCase type names / Sonar `java:S101`, …).

## When adding a feature

1. Place code in the correct context package (extend domain spec if new vocabulary).
2. Fire or observe CDI events for cross-context reactions; update [cdi-events.md](../../docs/cdi-events.md).
3. Do not add domain imports to `shared`.
